node.text: TX Gov. Greg Abbott is preparing to fight the Biden administration’s vaccine mandate for employers with over 100 workers. After Biden’s announcement, Gov. Abbott tweeted, “Biden’s vaccine mandate is an assault on private businesses.” Gov. Abbott will discuss his plan to combat Biden’s mandate TONIGHT on “Hannity.”

node.text: Today we remember those who perished in awful terror attacks on September 11, 2001. Twenty years ago today, our nation was changed and so was the world. The horrific images of that day will forever be in the minds and hearts of Americans.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sean Hannity on September 10, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text.

node.text: Twenty years ago, our nation entered Afghanistan to fight the terrorists who helped murder nearly 3,000 people on September 11, 2001. Now, Americans and Afghan allies are trapped behind enemy lines as Taliban terrorists take over the country. TONIGHT on “Hannity,” Rep. Ronny Jackson and Reince Priebus will reflect on the anniversary of 9/11 and Biden’s botched Afghanistan withdrawal.

node.text: While touring a homeless encampment in Venice, CA, Larry Elder was attacked by a person in a gorilla mask, who threw eggs and yelled at the gubernatorial candidate. This would have been on the front page of every paper if he were a Democrat, but because Larry Elder is a Republican the media mob has been silent! TONIGHT on “Hannity,” Larry Elder will discuss the media’s silence on the attack and the recall election.
